                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.51/93.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Silliman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-29T05:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 29, 1914, 5 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s August 28, 5 p.m. The attitude of the present Governmental
                    organization in Mexico is decidedly unfriendly towards all Catholic schools.
                    While there may not be so much expulsion as heretofore it is not expected that
                    schools will be permitted to reopen at any time in the near future.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
